AWKA  – The Catholic Women Organ­isation, (C.W.O), Basilica of the Most Holy Trinity, Onit­sha, has presented an award of excellence to the wife of the Governor of Anambra State, Dr. Ebelechukwu Obiano, for her role in governance and charity. The Catholic women group, while presenting the award to the governor’s wife at Aguleri, said that Governor Willie Obiano’s eight years of stellar performance in the of­fice enjoyed strong support from his wife who used her charity organisation, Caring Family Enhancement Initia­tive (CAFÉ), to touch the lives of the indigent and less privi­leged persons positively. Before presenting the award to Mrs. Obiano, the President of CWO Basilica of the Most Trinity, Onitsha, Mrs. Ify Onochie, described the Governor’s wife as a great achiever who has set a remarkable record in philan­thropy and redefined the con­cept of charity. APC Crisis Deepens As Buhari’s Imposition Of Adamu, Others Tear… Obasanjo Remains Quintessential Leader At 85, Says Sanwo-Olu She noted that Mrs. Obi­ano has been consistent in advocacy for the protection of vulnerable women and children as well as in her practical works of charity in support of widows, the physically and mentally chal­lenged persons.